<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-05-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-05-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="124" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Dayton</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 564.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-05-31"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 31, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your despatch of the 16th
                            of May, No. 466, and I am gratified to learn that the explanations you
                            have made concerning the temporary inconveniencies resulting from the
                            postponement of the intended visit of French officers and from the
                            present suspension of the privilege conceded for the removal of French
                            tobacco have been made in so satisfactory a manner.</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">William L. Dayton</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>